    "instructions": [
        "Pat chicken dry and place in a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice, then coat evenly with paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. Let marinate for 10-15 minutes.",
        "To make the sauce: In a small saucepan, combine honey, chili flakes, vinegar, butter, and minced garlic. Simmer over medium heat for 2-3 minutes until bubbly and fragrant. Adjust spice level to taste.",
        "Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Sear chicken for 5-6 minutes per side for thighs (or 4-5 minutes for breasts) until cooked through and golden brown. Alternatively, bake at 400°F (200°C) for 20-25 minutes.",
        "Pour the hot honey sauce over the cooked chicken and top with disintegrated feta. Let it sit for a few minutes to allow the feta to slightly melt.",
        "Garnish with fresh herbs and lemon zest before serving. Serve with rice, couscous, or roasted vegetables."
